Create high-retention, addictive games with simple mechanics and strong reward loops.

🧠 Key Behavior Changes

Instead of just “building a game,” the agent will:
	•	Prioritize fun over features
	•	Focus on repeatable gameplay loops
	•	Optimize for engagement time + replayability

🔥 What It Emphasizes

Core Loop First

Every game must answer:

“What does the player do every 10 seconds?”

Example:
	•	Tap → earn coins → upgrade → repeat

⸻

Addictive Systems (REQUIRED)
	•	Progression (levels, upgrades)
	•	Rewards (coins, unlocks)
	•	Feedback (animations, sounds)
	•	Challenge (increasing difficulty)

⸻

Game Types It Defaults To
	•	Idle/clicker games
	•	Reaction/timing games
	•	Simple arcade loops
	•	Upgrade-based games

👉 Because these are easiest to make addictive quickly

⸻

Output Example Structure
	•	Game concept
	•	Core loop
	•	Systems (progression, rewards)
	•	Full code
	•	“Make it more addictive” upgrades

⸻

